              </p>  
                
              <p>
                We use the Squeeze Theorem to prove that <m> \lim_{(x,y) \to (0,0)} k(x,y) = 0</m>. Note that
                <me>
                   \frac{x^2y^4}{x^2 + y^2} = \left (\frac{x^2}{x^2 + y^2} \right ) y^4 \leq y^4,
